00:09:29,552 --> 00:09:31,813
point out on the graph where the weekly patches were.

240
00:09:31,953 --> 00:09:33,753
Well, they were every week all the way through there,

241
00:09:34,013 --> 00:09:34,814
and they made no difference.

242
00:09:34,874 --> 00:09:36,194
Like we never, and to this day,

243
00:09:36,234 --> 00:09:38,495
have never seen a rise in player numbers

244
00:09:38,535 --> 00:09:40,135
due to changing a small thing about the game.

245
00:09:40,175 --> 00:09:41,175
It's all about the big changes.

246
00:09:42,016 --> 00:09:43,556
So we switched to doing three weekly updates

247
00:09:43,576 --> 00:09:44,496
because one week patches

248
00:09:44,536 --> 00:09:46,137
just completely paralyze your studio.

249
00:09:46,197 --> 00:09:49,017
You dream about the patch cycle every day, and it's bad.

250
00:09:49,398 --> 00:09:50,818
Anyway, so at this point,

251
00:09:50,918 --> 00:09:53,239
we'd declined from 70,000 to 10,000 users.

252
00:09:53,279 --> 00:09:54,359
The business is still going well.

253
00:09:54,379 --> 00:09:55,559
We're making some money for once,

254
00:09:55,619 --> 00:09:56,420
and things are looking great.

255
00:09:57,514 --> 00:09:58,794
But we need to get our user numbers back up.

256
00:09:58,834 --> 00:10:01,595
We've tasted the sweet fruit of 70,000 concurrent users

257
00:10:01,655 --> 00:10:03,275
and being at the top of the Steam charts

258
00:10:03,295 --> 00:10:03,915
and all that kind of stuff,

259
00:10:03,975 --> 00:10:04,896
and we need to get back up there.

260
00:10:05,456 --> 00:10:06,456
And so we figured, well,

261
00:10:06,876 --> 00:10:08,416
we know that economy resets are important.

262
00:10:08,436 --> 00:10:10,017
They were critically important in Diablo II,

263
00:10:10,037 --> 00:10:11,217
so let's release some leagues.

264
00:10:11,317 --> 00:10:12,917
And the way leagues work in Path of Exile

265
00:10:13,357 --> 00:10:14,958
is that they are basically economy resets.

266
00:10:14,978 --> 00:10:16,758
In this case, it's the Anarchy and Onslaught League.

267
00:10:17,178 --> 00:10:19,179
The Anarchy one adds some rogue exiles to the game,

268
00:10:19,199 --> 00:10:20,779
which are some bad guys you get to find occasionally,

269
00:10:20,799 --> 00:10:23,279
and Onslaught made the monsters attack

270
00:10:23,299 --> 00:10:24,040
and move more quickly.

271
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:29,263
We also put some challenges in there, and this logo is from the challenge t-shirt that we gave out to the top 50 people.

272
00:10:29,303 --> 00:10:32,905
And those t-shirts are like $1,500 on eBay now, I think? Anyway.

273
00:10:33,325 --> 00:10:39,029
So we gave some t-shirts out to the top players at the start, and this motivated people to perform well in these leagues.

274
00:10:39,369 --> 00:10:42,691
And so the result of this was a hefty 40% increase in player numbers.

275
00:10:42,711 --> 00:10:46,394
We released this content, 40% extra players come back, it's validated.

276
00:10:46,774 --> 00:10:52,217
Except when you look at it in the grand context, that's 40% of somewhere near the 10k mark, and then it declined below 10k.

277
00:10:53,078 --> 00:10:57,520
So we learned to ourselves, we learned that challenge leagues are important, they bring players back, people care,

278
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:59,801
but we did a really terrible job at marketing these.

279
00:10:59,881 --> 00:11:04,344
A lot of people don't even remember the release, we put them in, we just turned the leagues on basically with a thing on our website.

280
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:09,846
And so we learned that you have to bundle these economy resets with significantly marketable content,

281
00:11:09,886 --> 00:11:13,788
like new characters, new acts, all that kind of stuff, because then the players and journalists will want to talk about it.

282
00:11:14,149 --> 00:11:19,875
The good news is, since we entered open beta, we've been working on a new character and a new half of an act.

283
00:11:20,215 --> 00:11:22,338
And so that's what Path of Exile 1.00 was.

284
00:11:22,498 --> 00:11:28,244
This is the Scion character class, and that's the Act 3x, as we called it, second half of Act 3 in the background there.

285
00:11:28,524 --> 00:11:30,126
And this is the official 1.00 launch.

286
00:11:30,166 --> 00:11:33,009
And our goal was to get back up to 70,000 concurrent users and keep them.

287
00:11:33,610 --> 00:11:36,312
And so we launched on Steam, we dropped all this content in.

288
00:11:36,592 --> 00:11:38,574
And I have to note, you can't launch on Steam in 2013

289
00:11:38,634 --> 00:11:41,075
when it actually works really well for marketing.

290
00:11:41,116 --> 00:11:42,176
You can't do that every day.

291
00:11:42,697 --> 00:11:44,338
And nor can you make this amount of content every day.

292
00:11:44,358 --> 00:11:44,998
It took a long time.

293
00:11:45,899 --> 00:11:46,380
Use the numbers.

294
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,321
Back up to 70K just like we wanted.

295
00:11:49,222 --> 00:11:50,723
Holding steady, we're feeling really good.

296
00:11:50,783 --> 00:11:52,624
This time we know what we're doing, got a lot of experience.

297
00:11:52,644 --> 00:11:53,785
The numbers are staying up there.

298
00:11:54,145 --> 00:11:54,666
It's awesome.

299
00:11:56,196 --> 00:11:57,497
Okay, so they went down again, that's fine,

300
00:11:57,997 --> 00:11:58,757
games do this, right?

301
00:11:58,777 --> 00:11:59,838
Like everyone's game goes down.

302
00:12:00,218 --> 00:12:01,819
And that bump there is Christmas, by the way.

303
00:12:02,619 --> 00:12:04,160
I don't have a pointer, but the one on the right

304
00:12:04,420 --> 00:12:05,721
is the effect of Christmas, if you're interested

305
00:12:05,741 --> 00:12:07,261
to see what that looks like in a declining game.

306
00:12:08,002 --> 00:12:09,862
So we realized here that we needed,

307
00:12:09,883 --> 00:12:11,403
it's the only thing that causes player numbers

308
00:12:11,423 --> 00:12:13,504
to ever go up, by the way, without releasing new content.

309
00:12:14,064 --> 00:12:15,905
Anyway, so we realized we needed more content.

310
00:12:15,925 --> 00:12:17,986
So we started work on our first Path of Exile expansion

311
00:12:18,026 --> 00:12:19,147
called Sacrifice of the Vile.

312
00:12:20,212 --> 00:12:22,373
Sacrifice of the Vaal introduced new endgame bosses

313
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:24,593
and introduced side areas and Vaal skill gems

314
00:12:24,653 --> 00:12:26,194
and a couple of new leagues and all the things

315
00:12:26,234 --> 00:12:28,094
a Path of Exile expansion needed roughly.

316
00:12:28,574 --> 00:12:29,154
And how did it do?

317
00:12:29,634 --> 00:12:31,075
Well, that's the bump on the right there.

318
00:12:31,095 --> 00:12:32,735
It's reasonable, we got some more users,

319
00:12:32,755 --> 00:12:33,895
we got some more money, things are good.

320
00:12:33,915 --> 00:12:36,396
Like I have to stress, morale at the company is excellent.

321
00:12:36,436 --> 00:12:38,556
We control our own destiny, everything's awesome,

322
00:12:38,576 --> 00:12:39,537
people are having a good time,

323
00:12:39,597 --> 00:12:41,037
it's great running this game as a service

324
00:12:41,057 --> 00:12:42,237
for almost every team member.

325
00:12:42,277 --> 00:12:43,398
It was their first released game.

326
00:12:43,738 --> 00:12:45,498
We're on top of the world and we're finding

327
00:12:45,518 --> 00:12:47,518
that releasing expansions bumps the player numbers up.

328
00:12:47,558 --> 00:12:48,799
So now we have a button we can push

329
00:12:48,819 --> 00:12:49,899
that makes the player numbers go up.

330
00:12:50,439 --> 00:12:51,761
So let's push it a bunch more times.

331
00:12:52,322 --> 00:12:54,604
We decided to scope out the second expansion to be bigger,

332
00:12:54,624 --> 00:12:58,789
because the key question is, what is the cadence and size that we need to hit for these Path of Exile expansions?

333
00:12:58,849 --> 00:13:00,591
Right? We're all scientists, we want to optimize this.

334
00:13:01,599 --> 00:13:02,980
So, Forsaken Masters comes along.

335
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,221
This is an expansion that augmented the game thoroughly

336
00:13:05,301 --> 00:13:06,942
all the way through with these master missions

337
00:13:06,983 --> 00:13:09,324
and there's like customizable player housing

338
00:13:09,364 --> 00:13:09,984
and that kind of stuff.

339
00:13:10,505 --> 00:13:11,305
It was a good expansion.

340
00:13:11,325 --> 00:13:12,606
And it took about five months to make.

341
00:13:13,447 --> 00:13:14,587
And during which time the player numbers

342
00:13:14,607 --> 00:13:15,648
were pretty flat down the bottom.

343
00:13:16,448 --> 00:13:17,429
But the spike was bigger.

344
00:13:17,689 --> 00:13:19,190
So bigger expansion, bigger spike.

345
00:13:19,230 --> 00:13:19,951
This is looking good.

346
00:13:19,991 --> 00:13:21,792
We have a bigger button we can press if we want to.

347
00:13:22,052 --> 00:13:23,713
But this is tricky because it took longer to make.

348
00:13:23,753 --> 00:13:25,214
So is it even worthwhile sitting at 10,000

349
00:13:25,674 --> 00:13:26,915
concurrent users for so long?

350
00:13:27,755 --> 00:13:30,496
So we decided that we would try an even bigger expansion

351
00:13:30,736 --> 00:13:32,716
while interleaving some smaller updates in.

352
00:13:33,277 --> 00:13:34,697
So we started work on,

353
00:13:34,797 --> 00:13:36,817
well, started work isn't completely correct

354
00:13:36,857 --> 00:13:38,938
because the ACT content guys have been working on this

355
00:13:38,958 --> 00:13:40,058
since we finished ACT 3X,

356
00:13:40,098 --> 00:13:42,959
but we formalized the Path of Exile The Awakening expansion,

357
00:13:42,979 --> 00:13:44,159
which is Path of Exile 2.00.

358
00:13:44,759 --> 00:13:46,020
It adds ACT 4 to the game.

359
00:13:46,300 --> 00:13:47,720
It adds a whole bunch of cool new stuff.

360
00:13:47,740 --> 00:13:49,660
There's socketable jewels that go in the passive tree.

361
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:51,641
We completely rewrote our networking code,

362
00:13:52,341 --> 00:13:53,921
all sorts of cool stuff that players were gonna love.

363
00:13:53,941 --> 00:13:55,002
And we didn't tell them about it yet

364
00:13:55,062 --> 00:13:56,462
because we're waiting until we can show them

365
00:13:56,482 --> 00:13:57,162
something impressive.

366
00:13:57,822 --> 00:14:01,885
And so this is going on in the background, and we know it's going to be a big spike, or at least that's the theory according to this.

367
00:14:02,165 --> 00:14:03,546
But let's try some stuff in the meantime.

368
00:14:04,567 --> 00:14:06,808
Two more leagues. This is Torment and Bloodlines.

369
00:14:06,928 --> 00:14:11,892
And we released these alongside some probably pretty misguided PvP stuff that we did in December of 2014.

370
00:14:12,372 --> 00:14:16,735
And they were okay. Like, the numbers jumped up again.

371
00:14:17,055 --> 00:14:19,197
Kind of proportional to the size of the content. In this case...

372
00:14:19,977 --> 00:14:23,363
In this case, the Torment and Bloodlines leagues were worthy of a spike about that big.

373
00:14:23,403 --> 00:14:26,467
Certainly not as important as the bigger spikes from the bigger updates.

374
00:14:26,648 --> 00:14:30,093
So far this is validating the thing. Release bigger content, get bigger spikes.

375
00:14:30,774 --> 00:14:33,117
But we're able to make them pretty easily while working on other stuff.

376
00:14:33,177 --> 00:14:34,159
So we're pretty happy with this.

377
00:14:35,003 --> 00:14:37,166
All right, next up is the one month league experiment,

378
00:14:37,346 --> 00:14:39,468
called being really desperate to get your players back

379
00:14:39,508 --> 00:14:40,629
and then calling it an experiment

380
00:14:40,669 --> 00:14:41,890
five years later retroactively.

381
00:14:42,431 --> 00:14:45,013
So we decided to try some one month leagues

382
00:14:45,053 --> 00:14:45,854
to see what would happen.

383
00:14:45,994 --> 00:14:47,816
The idea is we just put some cool game modes on there,

384
00:14:47,836 --> 00:14:49,177
it doesn't take a lot of development work,

385
00:14:49,458 --> 00:14:50,238
and we'll see what happens.

386
00:14:50,278 --> 00:14:51,740
Maybe one month is the ideal cadence

387
00:14:51,780 --> 00:14:52,821
for Path of Exile releases.

388
00:14:53,562 --> 00:14:55,283
So there's the two one-month leagues at the end there.

389
00:14:55,383 --> 00:14:56,664
It's hard to tell where the second one is.

390
00:14:57,024 --> 00:14:59,666
And this is because your players quickly get inoculated to this kind of stuff.

391
00:14:59,766 --> 00:15:02,448
One month is not enough time to play Path of Exile and enjoy all the stuff,

392
00:15:02,488 --> 00:15:03,669
especially for the slower players.

393
00:15:04,010 --> 00:15:05,771
There wasn't new content, there was no marketing.

394
00:15:05,811 --> 00:15:07,632
A lot of people here probably don't know we did them.

395
00:15:07,993 --> 00:15:09,514
The second one was Dark Shrine, by the way.

396
00:15:09,534 --> 00:15:11,175
A fan favorite with like 10 people.

397
00:15:11,195 --> 00:15:12,716
I mean, you can see it at the bump there.

398
00:15:13,077 --> 00:15:13,377
Anyway, so...

399
00:15:14,878 --> 00:15:17,240
This was kind of a failed experiment as far as we were concerned.

400
00:15:17,260 --> 00:15:19,982
It was keeping the players somewhat entertained, like the core audience was good,

401
00:15:20,042 --> 00:15:22,684
but you can see the graph there is trending downwards throughout 2014.

402
00:15:22,904 --> 00:15:25,086
This is the point where we're getting a little bit concerned.

403
00:15:25,126 --> 00:15:27,728
We're still over 10k, you know, we're still making money and it's profitable,

404
00:15:28,269 --> 00:15:29,309
but it's not looking great.

405
00:15:29,329 --> 00:15:30,690
Like, this is the point where we have to question,

406
00:15:30,731 --> 00:15:32,232
do we just make another game instead?

407
00:15:32,272 --> 00:15:32,932
Like, what's going on?

408
00:15:33,232 --> 00:15:34,714
But we had the Awakening coming out.

409
00:15:34,754 --> 00:15:35,995
That was Path of Exile 2.0.

410
00:15:36,035 --> 00:15:37,096
So that was the saving grace.

411
00:15:37,116 --> 00:15:38,216
We wanted to see how that performed.

412
00:15:39,368 --> 00:15:41,651
So, we finished The Awakening, got it released,

413
00:15:41,891 --> 00:15:44,295
and it had a big spike, exactly as we had expected

414
00:15:44,335 --> 00:15:45,376
because it was a lot of content.

415
00:15:45,396 --> 00:15:47,419
So this is like, everything on this graph says

416
00:15:47,439 --> 00:15:49,181
that the more work you do, the better the results are,

417
00:15:49,221 --> 00:15:50,883
which is great, that's a good moral to live by.

418
00:15:51,524 --> 00:15:53,707
And the problem was, this just wasn't sustainable for us.

419
00:15:54,028 --> 00:15:55,930
We had this awful situation where...

420
00:15:56,769 --> 00:16:00,173
We'd work really hard to release some stuff, the player numbers would spike up briefly,

421
00:16:00,193 --> 00:16:03,757
then they're back down to the borderline unprofitable mark, and we have to make more content.

422
00:16:03,797 --> 00:16:05,538
And we just get to press the button really infrequently.

423
00:16:05,819 --> 00:16:07,180
We wanted to change the whole paradigm.

424
00:16:07,641 --> 00:16:09,042
So let's look at what we've learned so far.

425
00:16:09,623 --> 00:16:13,066
Number one, economy resets. That's the key thing here for Action RPG.

426
00:16:13,367 --> 00:16:16,727
If you start a fresh server, everyone rushes in, they take time off work, they want to

427
00:16:16,747 --> 00:16:18,948
get to level 100 the fastest, they find all the good items.

428
00:16:19,348 --> 00:16:20,648
Economy resets are amazing.

429
00:16:20,988 --> 00:16:25,749
They're an opportunity to have a fresh start and a fair playing field for players.

430
00:16:25,989 --> 00:16:29,590
If you've disengaged from the game, the economy restart is the perfect time to get back into

431
00:16:29,670 --> 00:16:34,071
it because it lets you have an equal footing with other people who are much better than

432
00:16:34,111 --> 00:16:34,211
you.

433
00:16:34,251 --> 00:16:37,152
You believe you're better than them and everyone's happy until they're not.

434
00:16:37,792 --> 00:16:41,753
So economy resets were great. The next note was about small content patches.

435
00:16:41,853 --> 00:16:45,254
They never helped us in any way actually increase player numbers. Now don't get me wrong,

436
00:16:45,314 --> 00:16:50,376
releasing content is always good for the game, right? At the beginning when we're doing one weekly updates and adding new items and skills,

437
00:16:50,396 --> 00:16:53,457
that's vitally important to have the game actually have some content for people to play,

438
00:16:53,757 --> 00:16:57,478
but it never moved the numbers up. And the reason why is there are two benefits to content.

439
00:16:57,779 --> 00:16:59,200
The first one is it makes your game better,

440
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:00,581
and the second one is marketing.

441
00:17:00,841 --> 00:17:02,663
And you want marketing when you're doing this kind of thing

442
00:17:02,703 --> 00:17:03,764
and trying to get your graphs higher.

443
00:17:04,144 --> 00:17:05,085
And so it's very important,

444
00:17:05,105 --> 00:17:06,286
if you batch your content together,

445
00:17:06,326 --> 00:17:08,708
you get both the marketing and making the game better.

446
00:17:09,549 --> 00:17:10,770
So it's gotta be above a threshold

447
00:17:10,810 --> 00:17:11,971
of people wanting to talk about it.

448
00:17:11,991 --> 00:17:13,872
When we release Path of Exile expansions now,

449
00:17:13,992 --> 00:17:16,074
people will message each other excitedly to say,

450
00:17:16,114 --> 00:17:17,435
look at this cool stuff in Path of Exile.

451
00:17:17,495 --> 00:17:18,856
It goes to the top of overall Reddit.

452
00:17:18,876 --> 00:17:19,877
It does all that kind of good stuff.

453
00:17:20,438 --> 00:17:21,919
Back then, no one was calling anyone

454
00:17:21,939 --> 00:17:23,641
when you release a single new skill gem.

455
00:17:23,801 --> 00:17:25,642
And journalists were not covering it, but they are now.

456
00:17:26,523 --> 00:17:28,564
The next thing is balance changes during a league.

457
00:17:29,044 --> 00:17:30,525
If you decide you want to fix something,

458
00:17:30,545 --> 00:17:31,626
you know, to make the game better,

459
00:17:32,006 --> 00:17:33,807
then the people who are doing that thing will be angry.

460
00:17:34,067 --> 00:17:35,348
And if you make something more powerful

461
00:17:35,408 --> 00:17:36,188
because it was too low,

462
00:17:36,228 --> 00:17:37,929
the people not doing that thing are angry

463
00:17:37,949 --> 00:17:39,850
because they missed out on choosing that character build.

464
00:17:40,110 --> 00:17:42,772
And so basically making any kind of mid-season tweaks

465
00:17:42,872 --> 00:17:44,573
is just a very negative experience

466
00:17:44,593 --> 00:17:46,153
for a lot of players who care about fairness.

467
00:17:46,494 --> 00:17:48,155
And so we learned to push these balance changes

468
00:17:48,195 --> 00:17:49,095
to between the leagues,

469
00:17:49,355 --> 00:17:50,576
because that's the point when players

470
00:17:50,616 --> 00:17:51,756
are choosing what character to play.

471
00:17:51,776 --> 00:17:53,718
They can see what's been reduced and what's been improved

472
00:17:54,058 --> 00:17:55,258
and choose to play based on that.

473
00:17:56,606 --> 00:17:59,388
The final story is one that I did not realize myself.

474
00:17:59,588 --> 00:18:00,989
I wish I was smart enough to think of this,

475
00:18:01,049 --> 00:18:02,590
but this actually came from Kriparian,

476
00:18:02,610 --> 00:18:04,191
the awesome streamer who played a lot of

477
00:18:04,211 --> 00:18:05,412
Path of Exile at the time.

478
00:18:06,012 --> 00:18:07,633
And so Kriparian and I were chatting on Skype,

479
00:18:07,673 --> 00:18:10,094
as I like to say that we did, occasionally,

480
00:18:10,455 --> 00:18:11,856
and he said to me, you know what, Chris,

481
00:18:11,896 --> 00:18:13,717
I've got a lesson for you that really helped me

482
00:18:14,137 --> 00:18:14,777
with my streaming.

483
00:18:14,817 --> 00:18:16,859
He said, every day, I will wake up

484
00:18:16,899 --> 00:18:18,200
and I'll stream at a reliable time.

485
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:19,340
I'm there, right at that moment.

486
00:18:19,540 --> 00:18:21,121
And I'm gonna stream until a predictable time.

487
00:18:21,342 --> 00:18:22,702
And then I'm going to work on my highlights video,

488
00:18:22,722 --> 00:18:24,302
and I'm going to post that at a predictable time.

489
00:18:24,562 --> 00:18:26,423
And then I'm back tomorrow doing exactly the same thing.

490
00:18:26,443 --> 00:18:27,903
And I'm going to try not to take days off.

491
00:18:27,923 --> 00:18:29,443
I'm just going to stream at these times.

492
00:18:30,284 --> 00:18:32,084
And the reason he explained was because that way,

493
00:18:32,124 --> 00:18:33,504
when someone comes home from work

494
00:18:33,524 --> 00:18:34,724
and they're wanting to watch Kripparian,

495
00:18:34,765 --> 00:18:36,185
if that's the time of day that he's streaming,

496
00:18:36,285 --> 00:18:37,125
then they'll be able to watch him.

497
00:18:37,145 --> 00:18:38,805
And if they want to watch a video before they go to bed

498
00:18:38,825 --> 00:18:40,666
or whatever the timing is, it will be there.

499
00:18:40,906 --> 00:18:42,006
And the day that it's not there

500
00:18:42,046 --> 00:18:43,386
is the day they look on the internet and say,

501
00:18:43,406 --> 00:18:44,147
what will entertain me?

502
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:45,187
What else is there in the world?

503
00:18:45,207 --> 00:18:46,367
And they'll find some other thing,

504
00:18:46,407 --> 00:18:48,087
maybe another streamer, maybe a TV show.

505
00:18:48,107 --> 00:18:49,728
And now that's the thing they're doing for entertainment.

506
00:18:50,148 --> 00:18:54,173
and he felt that his numbers dropped significantly if he deviated from his very rigid schedule.

507
00:18:54,653 --> 00:18:57,237
Now, you know, he's a powerhouse of streaming, right? He's amazing.

508
00:18:57,677 --> 00:19:00,761
And he recommended that we do a similar schedule with Path of Exile.

509
00:19:01,101 --> 00:19:03,964
Because he said, look at your graph of what you've actually done in 2014.

510
00:19:04,645 --> 00:19:07,028
I made this graph, not him. But this is...

511
00:19:07,989 --> 00:19:11,712
It was all over the place, right? We've got medium leagues at 20 weeks, big ones at 16,

512
00:19:11,752 --> 00:19:15,796
they arbitrarily get small and close together. No Path of Exile player is going to think anything

513
00:19:15,876 --> 00:19:18,998
other than, is that game dying? Like, what's going on with them getting smaller and what's

514
00:19:19,018 --> 00:19:23,242
with the timing? No one can predict anything. And so he strongly suggested we have a rigid schedule

515
00:19:23,522 --> 00:19:26,244
because that way it's more convenient for him because then he knows when to stream it,

516
00:19:26,445 --> 00:19:29,347
but it's also convenient for everyone else. And so we tried this out.

517
00:19:30,768 --> 00:19:32,930
So this was our new schedule, the new era of leagues,

518
00:19:32,990 --> 00:19:33,510
as it's called.

519
00:19:33,750 --> 00:19:35,111
And so they're every 13 weeks.

520
00:19:35,131 --> 00:19:37,512
So this means exactly four of them fit into a year.

521
00:19:37,592 --> 00:19:39,173
That means that we know that they're going to be

522
00:19:39,233 --> 00:19:41,475
on the second weekend of the final month

523
00:19:41,535 --> 00:19:42,775
in each quarter or whatever we do.

524
00:19:42,795 --> 00:19:44,456
And this perfectly fits having one a few weeks

525
00:19:44,496 --> 00:19:46,718
before Christmas and a week before GDC

526
00:19:46,798 --> 00:19:47,798
and a week before E3.

527
00:19:47,978 --> 00:19:49,819
It just matches everything and it's great.

528
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:51,801
So we started doing this and we were initially

529
00:19:51,821 --> 00:19:52,641
doing some pipelining.

530
00:19:52,681 --> 00:19:54,962
We work on a small one while working on a bigger one

531
00:19:54,982 --> 00:19:55,623
in the background.

532
00:19:55,703 --> 00:19:57,004
And then in the second part of the cycle,

533
00:19:57,024 --> 00:19:58,805
we release the big one and then repeat this.

534
00:19:59,125 --> 00:20:01,308
And that enabled us to experiment with scope and so on,

535
00:20:01,328 --> 00:20:03,813
because at this point we still weren't 100% sure

536
00:20:03,873 --> 00:20:05,796
how large these had to be to have the correct effect.

537
00:20:06,096 --> 00:20:07,278
We were pretty sure 13 weeks,

538
00:20:07,298 --> 00:20:09,722
which is roughly three months, was the right amount of time.

539
00:20:11,265 --> 00:20:12,527
So, that was the new schedule.

540
00:20:13,719 --> 00:20:17,262
Now the key philosophy here is players will stop playing your game.

541
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:18,183
That's unavoidable.

542
00:20:18,303 --> 00:20:20,606
At some stage something's going to happen that makes them stop playing.

543
00:20:20,646 --> 00:20:23,929
They get a new job or whatever, they get burned out, another game comes along.

544
00:20:24,130 --> 00:20:26,893
But the key thing is to give them a lot of opportunity to re-engage.

545
00:20:26,913 --> 00:20:29,636
And that means they have to really clearly know when the next coming back.

546
00:20:30,096 --> 00:20:33,760
It is inexcusable for a player to be able to leave your game without knowing the date

547
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:36,102
that they are returning to it, as far as we're concerned with this.

548
00:20:36,603 --> 00:20:39,285
And so that's why we want to make sure that users quit with a plan to come back.

549
00:20:39,565 --> 00:20:41,967
Because before we clearly signaled when the next release was,

550
00:20:42,247 --> 00:20:45,069
players would get horribly burnt out and then they would just never play again.

551
00:20:45,089 --> 00:20:47,490
Whereas now, they can quit before they get burnt out.

552
00:20:47,530 --> 00:20:50,192
They can say, you know what, I've finished this league, I've seen this stuff,

553
00:20:50,453 --> 00:20:51,593
I'll just come back for the next one.

554
00:20:51,894 --> 00:20:54,015
And that's amazing for us because then the users are fresh,

555
00:20:54,055 --> 00:20:56,977
they get chances to play their AAA games or Fortnite or whatever they do,

556
00:20:57,437 --> 00:20:58,758
and it works really well.

557
00:20:59,199 --> 00:21:01,800
Also, we monetize very heavily towards the start of our leagues.

558
00:21:01,840 --> 00:21:05,223
That's where we introduce new cosmetic microtransactions and supporter packs and so on.

559
00:21:05,523 --> 00:21:08,165
So it honestly doesn't matter a lot if we lose users right at the end,

560
00:21:08,806 --> 00:21:11,508
because they'll come back and monetize again at the beginning of the next league.

561
00:21:12,467 --> 00:21:13,668
So let's have a look at some results.

562
00:21:14,209 --> 00:21:15,871
So this tiny little bump at the bottom

563
00:21:16,031 --> 00:21:18,454
is the same size as roughly Forsaken Masters was.

564
00:21:18,534 --> 00:21:20,616
Just for, I've rescaled this because it's foreshadowing.

565
00:21:20,997 --> 00:21:22,979
Anyway, so this was Talisman, right?

566
00:21:23,019 --> 00:21:24,922
Talisman was a great league, it was a decent size.

567
00:21:25,022 --> 00:21:26,984
If we could release Talisman every three weeks,

568
00:21:27,024 --> 00:21:28,246
every three months, I'd be pretty happy.

569
00:21:28,666 --> 00:21:29,888
And so Talisman went well.

570
00:21:29,908 --> 00:21:31,490
And that was one of the small ones in our cycle.

571
00:21:32,230 --> 00:21:35,053
All right, so the next one was the Ascendancy slash Parandas update.

572
00:21:35,313 --> 00:21:38,136
This was a bigger one because as you saw, we're going small, big, small, big.

573
00:21:38,156 --> 00:21:40,859
So, so far there's no unexpected results, right? Small, big, all good.

574
00:21:41,419 --> 00:21:44,222
Next one is a small one again because it was Prophecy which wasn't as big.

575
00:21:44,562 --> 00:21:46,744
But you'll notice it was actually a little bit bigger than Talisman.

576
00:21:46,884 --> 00:21:48,726
So, this is how we rationalize. The numbers went down,

577
00:21:48,826 --> 00:21:51,409
but in a good way, right? Because they're bigger than the previous small one.

578
00:21:52,129 --> 00:21:53,810
And then sure enough, we released the next big one,

579
00:21:53,930 --> 00:21:54,690
nothing surprising.

580
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:56,551
This is Atlas of Worlds and Essence League.

581
00:21:56,931 --> 00:21:59,072
And at this point, we decided we hated pipelining

582
00:21:59,352 --> 00:22:01,553
because we're getting so much attention split

583
00:22:01,573 --> 00:22:02,333
between these two leagues.

584
00:22:02,373 --> 00:22:04,374
We wanted to see what happens if we just focus

585
00:22:04,394 --> 00:22:05,674
on one thing at a time and do it well.

586
00:22:05,954 --> 00:22:07,535
So we said, if we could make one thing, what would it be?

587
00:22:07,855 --> 00:22:09,696
So we made Breach, and Breach is very popular,

588
00:22:10,116 --> 00:22:11,297
and it was our best release ever.

589
00:22:11,697 --> 00:22:13,037
So then we said, well, what are we gonna make next?

590
00:22:13,077 --> 00:22:14,038
What about Legacy?

591
00:22:14,058 --> 00:22:15,538
So we made Legacy, best release ever.

592
00:22:16,379 --> 00:22:23,863
And at this point, the background process of making a new act that trundles along all ways in Path of Exile's background had Act V almost ready.

593
00:22:23,903 --> 00:22:28,425
That's the 3.0.0 expansion, the fall of Oriath, and that was sitting in our back pocket ready for release, so we did.

594
00:22:28,865 --> 00:22:31,067
And that was huge. Definitely our best release ever.

595
00:22:32,816 --> 00:22:33,936
We were feeling really good at this stage.

596
00:22:34,016 --> 00:22:35,717
User numbers are big, we just launched in China,

597
00:22:35,757 --> 00:22:37,538
we've just launched on Xbox.

598
00:22:37,838 --> 00:22:39,859
This is just PC here and it's already very high,

599
00:22:39,919 --> 00:22:41,219
dwarfing all our previous results.

600
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,020
And so the question is what would happen

601
00:22:43,040 --> 00:22:44,481
with our 13-week cycle going forward?

602
00:22:44,761 --> 00:22:46,842
Now we knew, and this happened,

603
00:22:46,882 --> 00:22:49,063
we knew that the next release would not be as tall as 3.0

604
00:22:49,583 --> 00:22:51,524
because it was just a regular 13-week cycle.

605
00:22:51,824 --> 00:22:53,184
It wasn't an entire expansion

606
00:22:53,224 --> 00:22:55,345
that took 18 months and 80 people to put together.

607
00:22:57,477 --> 00:22:59,238
The war for the Atlas one was not as big as 3.0,

608
00:22:59,718 --> 00:23:02,440
but it was bigger than the previous expansion before that.

609
00:23:03,121 --> 00:23:05,142
And then Bestry, and then Incursion,

610
00:23:05,202 --> 00:23:06,203
and it just keeps climbing.

611
00:23:06,243 --> 00:23:07,824
The 13-week cycle is working really well.

612
00:23:08,565 --> 00:23:10,066
Then we released Delve, which was great,

613
00:23:10,226 --> 00:23:11,407
and actually down a little bit,

614
00:23:11,467 --> 00:23:12,908
which we're not blaming on Delve,

615
00:23:12,988 --> 00:23:14,689
because it's probably a lack of retention

616
00:23:14,709 --> 00:23:16,070
during Incursion or something like that.

617
00:23:16,611 --> 00:23:18,092
And we're a little bit disappointed it was down.

618
00:23:18,112 --> 00:23:19,273
Like, this is the point we are questioning,

619
00:23:19,293 --> 00:23:21,114
you know, is this parabola finally, like, hit the top?

620
00:23:22,030 --> 00:23:23,671
But betrayal was really, really, really big.

621
00:23:24,171 --> 00:23:26,773
And so when you look at it in the context

622
00:23:26,913 --> 00:23:28,855
of all of the Path of Exile history,

623
00:23:29,075 --> 00:23:30,656
you can see that we were clearly declining.

624
00:23:30,676 --> 00:23:32,618
There's no argument about that for the first few years,

625
00:23:32,718 --> 00:23:33,999
and then really clearly climbing.

626
00:23:35,020 --> 00:23:36,981
And so this is the brunt of what I'm now gonna talk about

627
00:23:37,021 --> 00:23:37,822
for the rest of the talk,

628
00:23:38,282 --> 00:23:40,124
is what we do to actually make these,

629
00:23:40,604 --> 00:23:42,105
and how we scope them out,

630
00:23:42,165 --> 00:23:43,346
and how we deliver them fast enough.

631
00:23:44,487 --> 00:23:44,687
Okay.

632
00:23:46,664 --> 00:23:48,185
I'm gonna go through the marketing page

633
00:23:48,265 --> 00:23:49,566
for Path of Exile Synthesis,

634
00:23:49,606 --> 00:23:50,726
which is our most recent release.

635
00:23:50,886 --> 00:23:53,107
And what I'm gonna focus on specifically here

636
00:23:53,428 --> 00:23:55,709
is the way that we target specific groups

637
00:23:55,749 --> 00:23:56,609
of Path of Exile users.

638
00:23:56,629 --> 00:23:58,190
Because everyone likes something about the game,

639
00:23:58,430 --> 00:23:59,411
that's why they're playing it.

640
00:23:59,651 --> 00:24:01,492
And so we've identified a big set of categories

641
00:24:01,552 --> 00:24:02,472
of things that people enjoy.

642
00:24:02,512 --> 00:24:04,213
We've broken all the players into psychographics,

643
00:24:04,514 --> 00:24:06,615
and we're gonna target each one with a specific slide.

644
00:24:06,935 --> 00:24:08,616
And the goal here is when they're reading through the page,

645
00:24:08,636 --> 00:24:10,237
they'll look at the features, they'll say, oh this is cool.

646
00:24:10,417 --> 00:24:11,737
And then they'll find the thing that clicks for them.

647
00:24:11,757 --> 00:24:13,018
They'll find the reason they're playing,

648
00:24:13,258 --> 00:24:14,439
and they'll say, whoa, that's good.

649
00:24:14,519 --> 00:24:15,639
Okay, time to tell all my friends.

650
00:24:16,573 --> 00:24:20,638
So first of all we start setting the scene, the setting and the story and new characters and so on.

651
00:24:20,658 --> 00:24:24,682
And there are players who really like discovering about the story in a league.

652
00:24:24,743 --> 00:24:27,666
This is the thing that turns them on and makes them want to play, and so we lead with that.

653
00:24:27,906 --> 00:24:29,488
And at this point some players are going to say,

654
00:24:29,829 --> 00:24:33,673
OK, cool, this looks really nice. It's got this awesome blue portal and this dude and you can explore memories.

655
00:24:34,013 --> 00:24:35,215
I'm going to go and get excited about it.

656
00:24:36,212 --> 00:24:40,235
The next thing we do is we talk about a unique gameplay mechanic in combat that we've introduced.

657
00:24:40,275 --> 00:24:44,218
In this case, it's the ability to explore these decaying memories and run away from this wall of decay.

658
00:24:44,618 --> 00:24:48,241
And this is something that for many players, that changes completely how Path of Exile plays

659
00:24:48,281 --> 00:24:51,403
because now they're running away from the decay wall, they've got to use movement skills differently.

660
00:24:51,843 --> 00:24:54,245
And this is a thing which causes them to become excited

661
00:24:54,485 --> 00:24:57,407
because that group of players loves the idea of combat being slightly different.

662
00:24:58,332 --> 00:25:01,795
The next group of players don't necessarily care about the story, they don't necessarily

663
00:25:01,835 --> 00:25:04,878
care about combat, they care about long-term meta progression within a league.

664
00:25:04,918 --> 00:25:06,720
The concept of building something up over time.

665
00:25:07,100 --> 00:25:10,624
And so we often implement kind of meta mechanics in Path of Exile which are like games unto

666
00:25:10,644 --> 00:25:11,164
themselves.

667
00:25:11,625 --> 00:25:14,888
And this really appeals to types of players who want a meta layer on top of the regular

668
00:25:14,928 --> 00:25:15,248
gameplay.

669
00:25:16,158 --> 00:25:20,160
And so for example, in Synthesis, you could get these puzzle pieces that you connect together

670
00:25:20,180 --> 00:25:22,661
a bit like Carcassonne and explore the memory map with that.

671
00:25:22,701 --> 00:25:24,141
And this is entirely a meta mechanic.

672
00:25:24,161 --> 00:25:27,382
It doesn't have any impact on the actual moment-to-moment gameplay of the game.

673
00:25:27,623 --> 00:25:30,504
This just dictates how you access the advanced content of the league.

674
00:25:30,784 --> 00:25:34,025
And that really appeals to groups of players who want to make sure they're doing a different

675
00:25:34,125 --> 00:25:35,165
meta thing with each league.

676
00:25:36,476 --> 00:25:39,097
Next we have what I call endgame aspirational content.

677
00:25:39,137 --> 00:25:40,618
So these are like final boss fights.

678
00:25:40,658 --> 00:25:41,759
They're really hard to get to.

679
00:25:41,999 --> 00:25:44,740
You've got to do a lot of meta progression to get there.

680
00:25:44,760 --> 00:25:45,841
They're very difficult encounters.

681
00:25:45,861 --> 00:25:46,721
They've got good rewards.

682
00:25:46,741 --> 00:25:48,222
You have to learn the strategy of a fight.

683
00:25:48,262 --> 00:25:49,282
They're big multi-stage ones.

684
00:25:49,602 --> 00:25:51,303
And they take a lot of development time to make.

685
00:25:51,884 --> 00:25:54,325
And they're only accessed by maybe 10% of our players,

686
00:25:54,405 --> 00:25:56,226
the top players who can get through to the end of the game,

687
00:25:56,266 --> 00:25:57,426
get a chance to see this content.

688
00:25:58,167 --> 00:26:03,089
And you may ask yourself, why are you guys spending like 20% of your development effort on something that affects 10% of players?

689
00:26:03,530 --> 00:26:07,532
And the reason why is there are groups of players in there who want to know that there is content that only they can get to.

690
00:26:07,612 --> 00:26:10,874
Stuff that's actually hard and they're an exclusive club for being able to do it.

691
00:26:11,314 --> 00:26:17,417
And so those players will work incredibly hard to identify the content, work out how to get there, rush there as quickly as possible, build characters custom made for it,

692
00:26:17,798 --> 00:26:23,701
do time runs, try to do it in hardcore, try to do it without getting hit, all of these things, and then repeat it over and over to get all the good items.

693
00:26:24,141 --> 00:26:24,361
And so...

694
00:26:24,702 --> 00:26:27,264
we found that it's incredibly useful to have this end game content,

695
00:26:27,404 --> 00:26:30,426
even if not everyone gets a chance to experience it themselves,

696
00:26:30,806 --> 00:26:35,390
because there's a good strong overlap between streamers and these top 10% of players,

697
00:26:35,410 --> 00:26:37,251
because streamers are generally the better players in the game,

698
00:26:37,491 --> 00:26:40,594
and so they can consume this content on stream and everyone else can watch and think,

699
00:26:40,754 --> 00:26:43,276
oh, I wish I was that good, I wish I could get characters that strong

700
00:26:43,576 --> 00:26:45,398
and be able to play the top Path of Exile content.

701
00:26:45,818 --> 00:26:47,359
And so we try to appeal to that group there,

702
00:26:47,399 --> 00:26:51,102
which has a lot of overlap with the rest of the player base from an aspirational point of view.

703
00:26:52,093 --> 00:26:53,454
Next, we talk about league rewards.

704
00:26:53,634 --> 00:26:54,794
Everyone loves finding items,

705
00:26:54,834 --> 00:26:56,035
that's why they're playing these games,

706
00:26:56,155 --> 00:26:58,336
and so we introduce new rewards

707
00:26:58,997 --> 00:27:01,018
that synergize with existing systems in the game.

708
00:27:01,358 --> 00:27:03,419
And this is for players who want to improve their characters

709
00:27:03,459 --> 00:27:05,240
and find out how they're going to be subtly different

710
00:27:05,280 --> 00:27:06,341
in terms of what items they're getting.

711
00:27:06,361 --> 00:27:09,083
In this case, it's the fractured and synthesized items.

712
00:27:09,463 --> 00:27:10,383
We talk about crafting.

713
00:27:10,583 --> 00:27:12,184
There are Path of Exile players who love crafting.

714
00:27:12,204 --> 00:27:13,885
There are ones who will be really bored

715
00:27:13,925 --> 00:27:14,686
looking at all the other stuff

716
00:27:14,706 --> 00:27:15,726
until we talk about crafting,

717
00:27:15,766 --> 00:27:17,467
and then the world opens up with possibilities

718
00:27:17,507 --> 00:27:19,829
of what kind of stuff they can make using the new systems.

719
00:27:20,449 --> 00:27:22,291
And this is also important from a gameplay point of view.

720
00:27:22,371 --> 00:27:23,893
As any Path of Exile players know here,

721
00:27:23,953 --> 00:27:25,955
if you can get a head start on the crafting in the League

