814
00:30:38,113 --> 00:30:39,354
And that means making new areas,

815
00:30:39,374 --> 00:30:40,555
because you've got to go to new places.

816
00:30:40,855 --> 00:30:42,516
But the traditional way of making levels in games

817
00:30:42,556 --> 00:30:44,518
can be slow and involves placing a bunch of things around

818
00:30:44,558 --> 00:30:46,159
and involving artists and taking time.

819
00:30:46,479 --> 00:30:48,080
Let's try to make a level in 60 seconds.

820
00:30:49,041 --> 00:30:52,305
So, I load up the tool and I draw a line across horizontally, which is a river,

821
00:30:52,545 --> 00:30:55,488
and then I draw a path going downwards, which is the white path there,

822
00:30:55,508 --> 00:30:56,630
and then I put forest around it.

