958
00:36:20,869 --> 00:36:21,750
really put to a lot of work.

959
00:36:22,270 --> 00:36:24,031
So let's have a look at how we've done that in Path of Exile.

960
00:36:24,371 --> 00:36:25,592
These are the same area.

961
00:36:25,672 --> 00:36:27,534
On the right, we have like Kalm's lava cave,

962
00:36:27,574 --> 00:36:29,395
and on the left, we have a plateau area.

963
00:36:29,795 --> 00:36:31,617
Now, what we did is we removed the lava

964
00:36:31,657 --> 00:36:33,498
and changed the environment lighting so it looks different,

965
00:36:33,518 --> 00:36:34,439
but the tiles are the same.

966
00:36:34,459 --> 00:36:36,040
I think many of the textures are the same as well.

967
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:36,981
That was really fast to do.

968
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:40,861
Now this is why you shouldn't add a day-night cycle to your game like this.

969
00:36:40,961 --> 00:36:43,902
So many people make action RPGs and it's easy to add a day-night cycle.

970
00:36:43,942 --> 00:36:46,603
So they do, because look at how awesome it is on the trailer to have to show off the

971
00:36:46,663 --> 00:36:47,304
day-night cycle.

972
00:36:47,584 --> 00:36:52,225
But that means you're throwing away the ability to hide versions of areas that use a different

973
00:36:52,265 --> 00:36:53,486
environment elsewhere in the game.

974
00:36:53,726 --> 00:36:57,287
As long as they're far enough away and look sufficiently different, then people will not

975
00:36:57,327 --> 00:36:59,108
necessarily feel when they're playing through.

976
00:36:59,328 --> 00:37:01,929
The players don't care in principle that you've reused content, they expect it.

977
00:37:02,149 --> 00:37:03,249
But they care when they can notice it.

978
00:37:03,589 --> 00:37:05,676
And so if you have a day-night cycle for each of your areas,

979
00:37:05,917 --> 00:37:07,442
you've thrown away so many permutations

980
00:37:07,482 --> 00:37:09,669
you could use to add actual meaningful extra content

981
00:37:09,730 --> 00:37:10,372
elsewhere in the game.

982
00:37:11,717 --> 00:37:15,397
Here's another area where we took the icy glacier area,

983
00:37:15,457 --> 00:37:17,158
I think this is the ascent area,

984
00:37:17,438 --> 00:37:18,938
and we made it yellow and took the snow away

985
00:37:18,978 --> 00:37:19,858
and now we've got a desert.

986
00:37:20,178 --> 00:37:22,299
And so we do this extensively throughout the game.

987
00:37:22,399 --> 00:37:25,059
I think like acts six through 10 show a lot of examples

988
00:37:25,119 --> 00:37:27,740
of both this and actual new assets mixed together

989
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:29,320
in a way that's very hard to tell,

990
00:37:29,380 --> 00:37:31,301
but was actually very, very cost effective

991
00:37:31,321 --> 00:37:32,021
at making content.

992
00:37:32,801 --> 00:37:34,081
Here's another example with monsters.

993
00:37:34,922 --> 00:37:38,886
So on the left here you can see a green flying monster, you can see a spiker and a bone wheel skeleton.

994
00:37:39,346 --> 00:37:41,929
And at the top you can see a random portal frame made of metal.

995
00:37:42,209 --> 00:37:45,612
Now we had a sudden and urgent need for a pile of synthesis monsters that looked cool.

996
00:37:45,652 --> 00:37:49,716
So we said, that metal stuff looks cool, let's take that and let's put it on the rigs of the monsters on the left.

997
00:37:50,257 --> 00:37:53,838
And so sure enough, we immediately have instantly animated and rigged monsters we can use.

998
00:37:53,878 --> 00:37:57,239
And all we had to do was give them new names, give them new sounds, give them new effects,

999
00:37:57,299 --> 00:38:00,399
and give them new skills so they have a meaningful different combat interaction with the player.

1000
00:38:00,679 --> 00:38:02,720
And then suddenly we had our synthesis monsters sorted out.

1001
00:38:03,100 --> 00:38:06,781
To make monsters on the left involves spooling up an asset creation pipeline that involves

1002
00:38:06,841 --> 00:38:11,502
concepting and high poly models and low poly models and texturing and all that UV stuff.

1003
00:38:11,782 --> 00:38:12,503
And I don't know any of this.

1004
00:38:13,303 --> 00:38:17,187
Animation rigging the whole works, you know getting effects. It takes months to make monsters

1005
00:38:17,447 --> 00:38:19,089
But if you do this like cheap approach here

1006
00:38:19,289 --> 00:38:23,974
You can make stuff that looks different than what you have in the game at the moment or relatively quickly and

1007
00:38:24,074 --> 00:38:27,177
We often have to make monsters with days of notice when we're putting these leaks together

1008
00:38:27,217 --> 00:38:32,342
So techniques like this really help and the best thing is these synthesis monsters don't feel like reskins

1009
00:38:32,382 --> 00:38:35,745
They've got their own new skills and stuff. It isn't just a blue version of the flying thing

1010
00:38:35,765 --> 00:38:37,447
It's like a cool metal version of the flying thing

1011
00:38:38,595 --> 00:38:41,617
Okay, so now we're going to talk about content reuse, which is different than asset reuse.

1012
00:38:41,637 --> 00:38:44,818
Because I'm talking about taking like a wholesale block of content and reusing it.

1013
00:38:45,398 --> 00:38:47,639
So this is Breach, which I just showed you.

1014
00:38:47,939 --> 00:38:50,300
And in the regular game, you'd find these hands and fight the monsters,

1015
00:38:50,340 --> 00:38:51,741
and players understood it and they liked it.

1016
00:38:52,681 --> 00:38:53,062
And then we...

1017
00:38:53,062 --> 00:38:56,223
We turned the Breach League off and had them relatively scarce within the game, but it

1018
00:38:56,263 --> 00:38:58,323
was available as a reward for later elsewhere.

1019
00:38:58,383 --> 00:39:01,624
So when we did Incursion, sure enough, the Vile have been researching Breaches in the

1020
00:39:01,664 --> 00:39:04,005
Temple of Atzoatl, and so you find Breaches in there.

1021
00:39:04,025 --> 00:39:06,866
And when the player sees that purple hand, they immediately notice.

1022
00:39:07,266 --> 00:39:10,127
They know exactly what it means in terms of the fact they're about to get a big fight

1023
00:39:10,167 --> 00:39:12,168
and lots of monsters, lots of experience, lots of items.

1024
00:39:12,188 --> 00:39:13,188
They understand the rewards.

1025
00:39:13,468 --> 00:39:16,449
They understand that if you find Splinters inside the Breach, it lets you create Breach

1026
00:39:16,469 --> 00:39:20,491
Stones, which lets you go and fight some endgame meta stuff entirely by seeing a purple hand

1027
00:39:20,531 --> 00:39:20,671
there.

1028
00:39:21,623 --> 00:39:23,846
This is a breach inside the Delve content.

1029
00:39:23,866 --> 00:39:25,748
So deep underground, there's Purple Hands,

1030
00:39:26,068 --> 00:39:26,969
and we just chuck it in there,

1031
00:39:27,049 --> 00:39:29,472
and it's really, like, it's entirely positive for players.

1032
00:39:29,492 --> 00:39:30,312
They hit a whole system

1033
00:39:30,332 --> 00:39:31,554
that they really enjoy engaging with.

1034
00:39:32,355 --> 00:39:34,837
Here we have some Harbinger fight in the regular game

1035
00:39:34,857 --> 00:39:35,838
when that was a main league,

1036
00:39:36,078 --> 00:39:37,280
and sure enough, you get the same fight

1037
00:39:37,340 --> 00:39:38,381
deep underground in Delve,

1038
00:39:38,421 --> 00:39:39,402
where there's a Harbinger portal

1039
00:39:39,422 --> 00:39:40,383
that the monsters come out of,

1040
00:39:40,643 --> 00:39:41,544
and it means you get access

1041
00:39:41,564 --> 00:39:42,865
to all of the rewards for that league.

1042
00:39:43,800 --> 00:39:47,122
This gentleman here is called Kadiro. He gives you bro deals for awesome items.

1043
00:39:47,142 --> 00:39:50,984
He's like a traveling salesman and we used him in the Parandus League and in very little since then.

1044
00:39:51,284 --> 00:39:58,028
But when we're designing betrayals rewards, of course one of the 200 or 300 outcomes has to be Kadiro's in a cage and he's very happy to do a deal with you.

1045
00:39:58,388 --> 00:40:01,310
And this is cute because of course, like, why is he in a cage in this area?

1046
00:40:01,650 --> 00:40:05,332
But it was something the players really liked because now when they want access to the Kadiro content,

1047
00:40:05,592 --> 00:40:08,573
they know they can go and find him in this outcome and all of that stuff is available.

1048
00:40:08,994 --> 00:40:14,857
So we found that wholesale content reuse has been incredibly useful at both bolstering the rewards in the game,

1049
00:40:15,077 --> 00:40:16,878
but also making sure that players immediately say,

1050
00:40:16,918 --> 00:40:18,419
oh, I know this, I know this, it's going to be great.

1051
00:40:19,579 --> 00:40:22,481
Okay, so now is the time for us to talk about some more controversial lessons.

1052
00:40:22,501 --> 00:40:24,042
This is the point where I get labeled crazy.

1053
00:40:24,062 --> 00:40:26,543
Alright, so this is the quality curve.

1054
00:40:26,583 --> 00:40:27,744
This is relatively obvious.

1055
00:40:27,784 --> 00:40:29,305
You have your work versus quality thing.

1056
00:40:29,565 --> 00:40:30,645
And this has an asymptote.

1057
00:40:30,885 --> 00:40:33,067
That means that you can never get to 100% quality.

1058
00:40:33,087 --> 00:40:34,788
It's going to take infinitely long in terms of work,

1059
00:40:34,868 --> 00:40:36,889
because people want more and more and more fixes.

1060
00:40:37,269 --> 00:40:38,169
But you can get pretty close.

1061
00:40:38,850 --> 00:40:40,892
The question is how far along the curve do you go?

1062
00:40:40,932 --> 00:40:43,115
And when you're left with 13 weeks, you can't apply the

1063
00:40:43,155 --> 00:40:45,437
when-it's-done philosophy, and you have to pick somewhere.

1064
00:40:45,778 --> 00:40:47,620
So for example here, for 50% of the effort,

1065
00:40:47,640 --> 00:40:48,841
you get 90% of the quality.

1066
00:40:49,061 --> 00:40:51,444
Now I'm not saying to release games that are only 90% quality,

1067
00:40:51,624 --> 00:40:53,967
but the way you do it is by putting the quality in the right places.

1068
00:40:54,307 --> 00:40:55,428
Polish the things that matter,

1069
00:40:55,709 --> 00:40:57,551
and don't care about the stuff that doesn't matter.

1070
00:40:58,590 --> 00:41:02,472
Now this means that you have to make some very difficult decisions about what things to pay attention to

1071
00:41:02,532 --> 00:41:06,833
and therefore the best skill for a developer to have on your team is the ability to know what actually matters.

1072
00:41:07,313 --> 00:41:12,515
Relatively few people on the Path of Exile team are able to actually gauge that as accurately as we would like

1073
00:41:12,895 --> 00:41:17,257
and so it's very important that we do focus everyone's efforts on the things that really, really pay benefits

1074
00:41:17,977 --> 00:41:19,177
for the actual content we're releasing.

1075
00:41:19,458 --> 00:41:23,379
And this is also why we hire our player base to be in the QA team and Dev team

1076
00:41:23,399 --> 00:41:27,180
because Path of Exile players will understand what's important because they've played through it a whole bunch.

1077
00:41:27,522 --> 00:41:28,615
and know how they interact with it.

1078
00:41:30,103 --> 00:41:32,244
All right, pipelining, we tried it, we really did.

1079
00:41:32,324 --> 00:41:35,145
We wanted to have two or three releases on the go at once

1080
00:41:35,265 --> 00:41:36,265
and it just really failed.

1081
00:41:36,666 --> 00:41:38,006
And we found several problems with this.

1082
00:41:38,346 --> 00:41:39,927
The first one was that when we're focusing

1083
00:41:39,967 --> 00:41:41,207
on too many releases at once,

1084
00:41:41,647 --> 00:41:43,408
we always have an excuse to go and look at the other one

1085
00:41:43,428 --> 00:41:44,188
when things got hard.

1086
00:41:44,288 --> 00:41:46,769
If you assign a developer, do all this stuff for release A

1087
00:41:46,829 --> 00:41:48,690
and then maybe do this stuff for release B later,

1088
00:41:48,890 --> 00:41:50,270
they'll work on A like they're meant to

1089
00:41:50,590 --> 00:41:51,651
until they get stuck.

1090
00:41:51,951 --> 00:41:53,471
And instead of then solving the hard problem,

1091
00:41:53,711 --> 00:41:54,591
they would often say,

1092
00:41:54,611 --> 00:41:56,172
oh, well, there's some easy stuff I can do on B,

1093
00:41:56,212 --> 00:41:57,773
so I'll just work on that for a few hours instead

1094
00:41:57,813 --> 00:41:58,413
to clear my mind.

1095
00:41:58,753 --> 00:42:00,754
And that's great, but then A is completely stalled.

1096
00:42:00,994 --> 00:42:02,555
And when you have precious few weeks

1097
00:42:02,595 --> 00:42:03,576
in order to get this stuff done,

1098
00:42:03,856 --> 00:42:05,317
you really can't handle those stalls.

1099
00:42:06,237 --> 00:42:08,859
The second thing is, if you pipeline releases,

1100
00:42:08,939 --> 00:42:10,280
you do not have time to react

1101
00:42:10,300 --> 00:42:11,861
to what the game actually needs.

1102
00:42:12,821 --> 00:42:14,382
By the time it's apparent that the game

1103
00:42:14,422 --> 00:42:16,343
needs a new end game, you're like three quarters

1104
00:42:16,363 --> 00:42:17,904
of the way through making a new beginning to it

1105
00:42:17,944 --> 00:42:19,765
or something like that, because Reddit will suddenly decide

1106
00:42:19,785 --> 00:42:20,866
there is a thing that needs fixing.

1107
00:42:20,886 --> 00:42:22,547
And if you have the ability to say, yes sir,

1108
00:42:22,607 --> 00:42:23,888
and get that done in 13 weeks,

1109
00:42:24,208 --> 00:42:25,989
that's not even good enough some of the time for them.

1110
00:42:26,549 --> 00:42:29,933
But having to spend like, you know, oh wait, wait, we've got the next two expansions almost finished, kind of,

1111
00:42:29,973 --> 00:42:32,235
we'll do this one next year, it's just not going to work.

1112
00:42:32,335 --> 00:42:34,217
The game is on fire until that thing is fixed.

1113
00:42:36,330 --> 00:42:38,433
It's also important not to stall content for later.

1114
00:42:38,553 --> 00:42:40,074
We get into a situation where we're like,

1115
00:42:40,195 --> 00:42:41,896
we finished all the skills we said we were gonna make,

1116
00:42:41,916 --> 00:42:43,819
and we've got two extra ones that got out of prototyping

1117
00:42:43,839 --> 00:42:44,519
and they're kind of finished.

1118
00:42:44,699 --> 00:42:45,100
Do we wait?

1119
00:42:45,120 --> 00:42:46,401
Do we leave them for the next expansion

1120
00:42:46,441 --> 00:42:47,182
so we have less to do?

1121
00:42:47,503 --> 00:42:48,764
No, put them in the game now.

1122
00:42:49,064 --> 00:42:51,687
The game needs to be in its best form now, all the time,

1123
00:42:51,747 --> 00:42:52,988
because you don't get second chances.

1124
00:42:53,249 --> 00:42:54,891
As much growth as possible every league,

1125
00:42:55,191 --> 00:42:56,272
otherwise you'll start to decline.

1126
00:42:57,177 --> 00:42:59,241
People express concern about creativity here.

1127
00:42:59,461 --> 00:43:02,706
They say, look, Chris, you've got this plan for like another 10 years of Path of Exile

1128
00:43:02,746 --> 00:43:03,888
with four releases per year.

1129
00:43:03,908 --> 00:43:05,009
That's 40 more leagues.

1130
00:43:05,150 --> 00:43:06,331
I can think of two good ones.

1131
00:43:06,352 --> 00:43:07,794
Where are we going to get 40 from?

1132
00:43:08,274 --> 00:43:09,917
And I always refer them back to Magic the Gathering.

1133
00:43:10,921 --> 00:43:14,683
They have released new sets, four per year or whatever,

1134
00:43:14,963 --> 00:43:17,645
for so many decades now, like 26 years in or something,

1135
00:43:17,725 --> 00:43:19,986
hundreds of these things, and there's always new ideas.

1136
00:43:20,066 --> 00:43:22,068
It's amazing the fact they can go back to the well

1137
00:43:22,128 --> 00:43:23,709
and find really cool, compelling stuff.

1138
00:43:23,989 --> 00:43:25,970
And so whenever I hear that we're not gonna come up

1139
00:43:25,990 --> 00:43:27,551
with another 10 or 20 or 30 of these,

1140
00:43:27,591 --> 00:43:28,852
I go, they did 100, you know,

1141
00:43:29,352 --> 00:43:32,174
and I'm certain we'll be able to, the well will refill.

1142
00:43:33,020 --> 00:43:36,742
Now if you're a project manager, you're probably asking how we can make all of this stuff in 13 weeks.

1143
00:43:36,762 --> 00:43:39,744
Because it's not just we start work and in 13 weeks later we release it.

1144
00:43:40,264 --> 00:43:42,165
Consider how the schedule actually works in reality.

1145
00:43:42,565 --> 00:43:45,427
So we release the content and now there's problems with it, right?

1146
00:43:45,467 --> 00:43:49,169
Right now there's a bit of a fire where we're fixing some stuff with synthesis that the community didn't like.

1147
00:43:49,209 --> 00:43:50,890
That's cool, we'll have that fixed early next week.

1148
00:43:51,191 --> 00:43:53,532
But this has taken the first two weeks of the schedule to do so.

1149
00:43:54,072 --> 00:43:57,294
So there's some time spent doing live ops work on the existing release you've done.

1150
00:43:57,595 --> 00:43:59,095
Then you've got to prototype the new stuff, right?

1151
00:43:59,135 --> 00:44:01,617
Ideally that's a bit pipelined in there, but still it takes time.

1152
00:44:01,657 --> 00:44:04,259
It's going to be another week before we really know for sure what 3.7.0 is.

1153
00:44:04,279 --> 00:44:06,980
So that's three weeks gone. Ten weeks left.

1154
00:44:07,261 --> 00:44:11,203
And coming from the other end, we like to renounce our content three weeks before the end.

1155
00:44:11,263 --> 00:44:14,685
We put our page up, we get the players hyped, they have time to tell their friends, there's a countdown.

1156
00:44:14,725 --> 00:44:17,927
You know, it makes sense for people to book time off work. So that's three weeks gone there.

1157
00:44:18,828 --> 00:44:21,530
We then have to actually do a press tour where we show all the journalist stuff.

1158
00:44:21,570 --> 00:44:23,671
It's very important to actually do real marketing and PR.

1159
00:44:23,952 --> 00:44:27,094
So we spend two weeks showing all the people stuff and preparing the marketing page.

1160
00:44:27,134 --> 00:44:29,596
But in order to do this, we have to actually have content ready to show them,

1161
00:44:29,636 --> 00:44:31,497
like a trailer and slides and this kind of stuff.

1162
00:44:31,797 --> 00:44:32,498
And that takes a week.

1163
00:44:32,878 --> 00:44:35,700
So now we've got this like four or five week window in the middle

1164
00:44:36,020 --> 00:44:37,281
to actually make all of the stuff.

1165
00:44:37,881 --> 00:44:38,562
And that's difficult.

1166
00:44:39,430 --> 00:44:41,512
And that's where the next counterintuitive advice comes in.

1167
00:44:41,552 --> 00:44:43,774
This is how you get your art so quickly.

1168
00:44:44,375 --> 00:44:46,236
Create content you have no plan for.

1169
00:44:47,137 --> 00:44:49,039
We have themed assets that we commission

1170
00:44:49,119 --> 00:44:50,940
because we know one day we're keen to use them.

1171
00:44:51,181 --> 00:44:53,162
And a great example of this is with the Betrayal League.

1172
00:44:53,242 --> 00:44:55,324
We decided we're gonna make this very complicated

1173
00:44:55,725 --> 00:44:57,406
evil organization with 19 members

1174
00:44:57,426 --> 00:44:59,448
who all have backstories and they all look different

1175
00:44:59,468 --> 00:45:01,410
and they feel different from any Path of Exile characters

1176
00:45:01,430 --> 00:45:02,090
we've had so far.

1177
00:45:02,370 --> 00:45:04,833
But where are we gonna get 19 fully modeled, rigged,

1178
00:45:04,873 --> 00:45:05,493
voice acted?

1179
00:45:05,913 --> 00:45:08,494
fleshed out characters like that in three or four weeks.

1180
00:45:08,854 --> 00:45:11,375
And the answer was, we go to our giant store of content

1181
00:45:11,395 --> 00:45:12,655
that we just have because we made it,

1182
00:45:12,916 --> 00:45:14,176
and we pick a bunch of characters.

1183
00:45:14,496 --> 00:45:16,176
We're like, this is a microtransaction armor set.

1184
00:45:16,196 --> 00:45:18,097
We were gonna sell it, but if I put it on a bandit

1185
00:45:18,117 --> 00:45:20,298
and sell it in two years, this is a new character.

1186
00:45:20,778 --> 00:45:23,719
And so, we found, we have just a catalog

1187
00:45:23,739 --> 00:45:25,579
of Path of Exile stuff that the team have made

1188
00:45:25,639 --> 00:45:27,320
because they can slot it into the art pipeline,

