00:48:07,141 --> 00:48:08,902
And of course, I would love to answer any questions.

1260
00:48:09,803 --> 00:48:11,804
Timeline-wise, it looks like we have like five

1261
00:48:11,844 --> 00:48:14,545
or 10 minutes, so use the microphone

1262
00:48:14,805 --> 00:48:15,686
if you would like to ask something.

1263
00:48:27,711 --> 00:48:29,755
So first I just want to say thanks for making the game

1264
00:48:29,956 --> 00:48:35,046
I've been playing since open beta and every league since it's just incredible kind of inspired me to enter this industry

1265
00:48:35,086 --> 00:48:36,589
but my question is that

1266
00:48:37,230 --> 00:48:39,611
You talk about reusing content and Path of Exile now.

1267
00:48:39,852 --> 00:48:41,973
There's so many options in end game, right?

1268
00:48:41,993 --> 00:48:43,314
It used to be just grinding maps,

1269
00:48:43,394 --> 00:48:45,436
but now we have lots of these meta systems

1270
00:48:45,456 --> 00:48:46,276
that we can engage in.

1271
00:48:47,737 --> 00:48:49,278
And I'm curious, with player retention,

1272
00:48:49,318 --> 00:48:50,900
games like Warframe allow players to

1273
00:48:51,240 --> 00:48:53,341
very specifically choose what they go into, right?

1274
00:48:53,361 --> 00:48:55,223
They're like, I want to grind out this meta system

1275
00:48:55,303 --> 00:48:56,284
and make a lot of progress there,

1276
00:48:56,324 --> 00:48:58,505
but in Path of Exile it feels widespread.

1277
00:48:58,545 --> 00:49:00,707
Like you kind of progress in all things slowly

1278
00:49:00,747 --> 00:49:01,988
as you work through the end game map system.

1279
00:49:02,008 --> 00:49:03,449
So I'm wondering if you have any opinions on

1280
00:49:04,169 --> 00:49:08,312
Path of Exile going forward in regards to allowing more player choice in what types

1281
00:49:08,372 --> 00:49:11,915
of previous league content they engage in throughout their experience in the endgame?

1282
00:49:12,495 --> 00:49:12,695
Right.

1283
00:49:13,056 --> 00:49:16,438
Okay, to repeat the question just for the recording, so you're basically asking, in

1284
00:49:16,838 --> 00:49:20,401
Path of Exile there's a lot of content in the endgame and you get access to it as you

1285
00:49:20,461 --> 00:49:20,841
find it.

1286
00:49:20,981 --> 00:49:25,104
It's very hard to actually focus on narrowing down to specific content you want to engage

1287
00:49:25,165 --> 00:49:25,205
in.

1288
00:49:25,565 --> 00:49:28,048
So this is something we've been experimenting with in the last few leagues.

1289
00:49:28,468 --> 00:49:31,772
We introduced Scarabs in the Betrayal League, which is something that's a tradable way of

1290
00:49:31,832 --> 00:49:34,195
augmenting the amount of a specific type of content that you find.

1291
00:49:34,635 --> 00:49:37,559
This is something we are planning to work on more because we do think that someone being

1292
00:49:37,579 --> 00:49:38,960
able to specialize is an important thing.

1293
00:49:39,301 --> 00:49:41,563
It's kind of like a trade skill or profession in another game.

1294
00:49:41,603 --> 00:49:44,927
If you're just a really good person at playing delve content or synthesis content,

1295
00:49:45,167 --> 00:49:47,068
that's something that's good for you to have a specialization in.

1296
00:49:47,088 --> 00:49:49,128
So this is a direction I would like us to go further,

1297
00:49:49,368 --> 00:49:51,609
but we are very careful, because everything here is tradable.

1298
00:49:51,829 --> 00:49:54,529
If we go slightly over the line, suddenly everyone is doing exactly that

1299
00:49:54,589 --> 00:49:57,470
and farming the optimal thing, and it's hard to get items out of the economy

1300
00:49:57,550 --> 00:50:00,631
once you've put them there. So we're probably too cautious with addressing that.

1301
00:50:00,651 --> 00:50:02,831
Hey, thank you so much for the talk.

1302
00:50:02,871 --> 00:50:05,692
How do you keep your team engaged with working on a game this long?

1303
00:50:06,322 --> 00:50:09,143
So the question is how we keep our team engaged for working on a game this long.

1304
00:50:09,384 --> 00:50:11,725
It helps to be the only big game development company in New Zealand.

1305
00:50:11,985 --> 00:50:12,565
I'm kidding.

1306
00:50:13,005 --> 00:50:16,867
Our team have amazing, amazing staff retention.

1307
00:50:16,907 --> 00:50:18,828
We love working with them, we treat them as well as we can

1308
00:50:18,948 --> 00:50:20,228
and it really helps.

1309
00:50:21,054 --> 00:50:26,037
To them, we're not necessarily working on Path of Exile for this long, but we're working on these 13 week game jams

1310
00:50:26,277 --> 00:50:29,759
where we're releasing new things. Like last year we said, who likes Pokemon? We all like Pokemon, let's do Beastory.

1311
00:50:29,959 --> 00:50:34,541
And we made a league based on that. And the team we're engaging, they're drawing the art for the little book that you can tick them all off.

1312
00:50:34,601 --> 00:50:39,143
And everyone's having a great time. And it's the frequent release cycles which let us actually, like, kind of,

1313
00:50:39,463 --> 00:50:44,766
everyone, when you join the Path of Exile team, you get an experience of designing and working on and releasing and then maintaining

1314
00:50:45,086 --> 00:50:47,027
a complete game four times a year, basically.

1315
00:50:47,448 --> 00:50:47,908
Awesome, thank you.

1316
00:50:49,158 --> 00:50:51,561
All right, so you have told us about your numbers

1317
00:50:51,601 --> 00:50:54,103
and how did you manage them on your own efforts, right?

1318
00:50:54,403 --> 00:50:57,806
But I subjectively think that it's

1319
00:50:57,866 --> 00:51:01,649
because of yours, good decisions,

1320
00:51:01,689 --> 00:51:03,811
while your competition was not doing really well.

1321
00:51:03,891 --> 00:51:06,273
So I feel obligated to ask the question,

1322
00:51:06,333 --> 00:51:11,498
how did the out of season, April Fool joke, actually,

1323
00:51:11,898 --> 00:51:14,440
that happened in BlizzCon actually affected Path of Exile?

1324
00:51:14,460 --> 00:51:15,501
I have a graph.

