00:51:55,964 --> 00:51:56,705
and covering so much.

1345
00:51:58,227 --> 00:52:00,290
My question is about one of the pillars

1346
00:52:00,310 --> 00:52:01,231
you talked about in the beginning

1347
00:52:01,351 --> 00:52:03,614
about a good RNG item system.

1348
00:52:04,235 --> 00:52:06,078
Could you talk about some common problems

1349
00:52:06,158 --> 00:52:08,000
or things not to do that maybe you've seen

1350
00:52:08,040 --> 00:52:09,502
in the industry or that you guys encountered

1351
00:52:09,642 --> 00:52:10,463
with these item systems?

1352
00:52:10,846 --> 00:52:13,588
So you're wanting to hear about some problems with item systems that other games do.

1353
00:52:13,888 --> 00:52:17,090
This is like, getting to know me in person is hearing about this stuff forever.

1354
00:52:17,530 --> 00:52:18,611
Um, okay, so...

1355
00:52:19,471 --> 00:52:22,093
In my opinion, the biggest mistake that games make with their item systems

1356
00:52:22,133 --> 00:52:24,754
is they have item mods that are individually hard to feel.

1357
00:52:24,994 --> 00:52:27,836
Like, the goal with Path of Exile is if you strip your character down to be pretty simple,

1358
00:52:28,036 --> 00:52:29,637
and you put an item on without looking at the mods,

1359
00:52:29,677 --> 00:52:33,079
you should be able to play and say what the mods do based on how the game feels.

1360
00:52:33,139 --> 00:52:34,480
Now this isn't something we always meet.

1361
00:52:34,540 --> 00:52:36,621
Obviously there's 11,000 stats in the game,

1362
00:52:36,661 --> 00:52:37,721
so it's hard to meet it with all of them.

1363
00:52:38,022 --> 00:52:39,502
But the core thing is we want them

1364
00:52:39,522 --> 00:52:40,923
to individually be impactful.

1365
00:52:41,223 --> 00:52:43,184
There's none of this like, plus one strength,

1366
00:52:43,224 --> 00:52:44,145
what does that even mean?

1367
00:52:44,285 --> 00:52:45,766
You know, we make sure the amount of strength

1368
00:52:45,786 --> 00:52:47,186
is actually meaningfully increasing your life,

1369
00:52:47,266 --> 00:52:50,228
meaningfully making at least 5% boost to damage

1370
00:52:50,248 --> 00:52:51,088
so you can feel the difference.

1371
00:52:51,569 --> 00:52:52,409
That's one example there.

1372
00:52:52,710 --> 00:52:54,732
Another example of what people do with their item systems

1373
00:52:54,972 --> 00:52:57,074
is they'll come up with a basically set of sequential items

1374
00:52:57,114 --> 00:52:59,176
where you can get this one, then you get this one, then you get this one.

1375
00:52:59,396 --> 00:53:00,958
And this is setting up a content train

1376
00:53:01,238 --> 00:53:02,940
that players, when they get the top item,

1377
00:53:02,960 --> 00:53:04,782
they're then saying, well, what is there to find now?

1378
00:53:04,842 --> 00:53:06,844
And you as the developer have to go and add more items on the end.

1379
00:53:07,304 --> 00:53:09,266
In Path of Exile, we go, yeah, there's random mods.

1380
00:53:09,486 --> 00:53:10,927
You'll get a top 10% item, you get a top 8%,

1381
00:53:11,387 --> 00:53:14,129
maybe a top 5%, but we believe that there are not,

1382
00:53:14,389 --> 00:53:17,111
like, the best items that were possible in 2013

1383
00:53:17,191 --> 00:53:18,872
have not necessarily been found yet

1384
00:53:18,912 --> 00:53:19,813
in any reasonable numbers,

1385
00:53:20,133 --> 00:53:21,794
just because of the harsh diminishing returns.

1386
00:53:22,134 --> 00:53:23,715
So to some extent, the initial levels

1387
00:53:23,995 --> 00:53:26,817
and mods that we set up six years ago are still working

1388
00:53:26,857 --> 00:53:29,079
and we haven't had to go and pile on additional higher mods

1389
00:53:29,119 --> 00:53:31,180
in Path of Exile, at least not to any large degree.

1390
00:53:31,200 --> 00:53:33,762
Thank you.

1391
00:53:33,782 --> 00:53:34,703
Hello, and thank you for the talk.

1392
00:53:35,423 --> 00:53:41,585
So you guys mentioned that your motivation for making this game was traditional boxed games like Diablo 2 and so on.

1393
00:53:42,065 --> 00:53:46,026
There the monetization model is well you like the game, you buy it and you enjoy it.

1394
00:53:46,626 --> 00:53:49,007
But for you guys it was not that sort of model.

1395
00:53:49,547 --> 00:53:53,488
It was mostly external visual updates and so on.

1396
00:53:53,848 --> 00:53:57,489
Moreover, a point of innovation I believe was your support packs.

1397
00:53:57,909 --> 00:54:01,390
Could you tell us a little bit about how you derived that business model?

1398
00:54:01,722 --> 00:54:06,084
That's a great question. So the question was, given that the other action RPGs were premium paid games,

1399
00:54:06,144 --> 00:54:09,445
why did we go free to play, have cosmetic microtransactions and supporter packs?

1400
00:54:10,025 --> 00:54:13,306
It was our plan to go free to play before that was a thing. We wanted to be the first free game.

1401
00:54:13,466 --> 00:54:17,547
It sounds silly, but that was 2006. We'd seen MapleStory, they were making a lot of money in Korea,

1402
00:54:17,727 --> 00:54:19,668
and we thought we'd revolutionize the Western gaming market.

1403
00:54:19,728 --> 00:54:22,691
Now I try not to say this because it's dumb because then if you spend seven years making the game

1404
00:54:22,731 --> 00:54:27,255
Everyone's free to play by the time you release in fact when we did release free to play was a bad phrase that you say

1405
00:54:27,275 --> 00:54:30,399
Free to play they assume bad monetization. We lost users by saying we were free

1406
00:54:30,639 --> 00:54:33,522
We tried very hard to make it seem you've got to pay for it anyway

1407
00:54:34,683 --> 00:54:40,028
So the ethical cosmetic microtransactions thing was because when we initially scoped the game out that was the only thing that made sense

1408
00:54:40,088 --> 00:54:43,311
We didn't realize that selling power was even this possible strategy, right? So

1409
00:54:44,192 --> 00:54:48,855
We scoped this out because it's a competitive game, people want to play a fair playing field,

1410
00:54:49,136 --> 00:54:52,598
and that was the way to design games. And thankfully this is now, you know, the tide

1411
00:54:52,618 --> 00:54:56,100
has turned on this to the point where most new games coming out these days are doing proper

1412
00:54:56,140 --> 00:55:00,383
ethical microtransactions in a good way if they're competitive. The Supporter Packs thing was we

1413
00:55:00,423 --> 00:55:04,246
needed to, we were about to start selling beta access in 2012 because we wanted to trickle a

1414
00:55:04,286 --> 00:55:06,947
few more people in and they were spamming us with threats if we didn't let them in,

1415
00:55:06,987 --> 00:55:07,928
so we figured we may as well take $10.

1416
00:55:08,769 --> 00:55:11,492
And so we made a page where you can spend $10 to get beta access.

1417
00:55:11,812 --> 00:55:14,115
And then we realized, considering Kickstarter was so big,

1418
00:55:14,175 --> 00:55:15,817
why not model it like what they were doing?

1419
00:55:16,038 --> 00:55:18,961
And so we added the $20 pack, and the $50 pack, and the $100 pack,

1420
00:55:18,981 --> 00:55:19,903
and we just kept going to $1,000.

1421
00:55:19,943 --> 00:55:23,647
And then that sold a lot of copies and gave us a lot of obligations

1422
00:55:23,687 --> 00:55:25,429
that we had to then fulfill for many years.

1423
00:55:26,771 --> 00:55:29,975
We've iterated now, I think we're on our 12th or 13th set of these supporter packs,

1424
00:55:30,135 --> 00:55:33,158
and it's something I also care a lot about, is supporter pack design.

1425
00:55:33,178 --> 00:55:37,783
So if you're doing anything on Kickstarter or other games where you're doing like a founder pack or supporter pack modeling,

1426
00:55:37,803 --> 00:55:40,326
and you want advice, I would love to give advice on that. I have opinions there.

1427
00:55:40,906 --> 00:55:42,348
Anyway, there's the summary of that.

1428
00:55:42,368 --> 00:55:43,289
Thank you.

1429
00:55:45,631 --> 00:55:45,731
Cool.

1430
00:55:46,829 --> 00:55:49,170
So, thanks again for making this game and this talk.

1431
00:55:49,230 --> 00:55:50,370
It's all amazing.

1432
00:55:50,810 --> 00:55:54,011
I play this game a lot, and I've been the guy

1433
00:55:54,071 --> 00:55:56,231
who is like, I'm done, but I'll play next league a lot.

1434
00:55:56,311 --> 00:55:57,932
And the question I have is,

1435
00:55:57,972 --> 00:56:00,632
how do you think about burnout burnout?

1436
00:56:01,733 --> 00:56:03,913
In this, like, you have these four releases a year,

1437
00:56:04,073 --> 00:56:06,734
you, people are ready to, like, come back,

1438
00:56:06,934 --> 00:56:07,854
and they're ready to come back,

1439
00:56:08,234 --> 00:56:10,995
but have you thought, like, what's the take on,

1440
00:56:11,515 --> 00:56:14,616
is, like, what if people run out of wanting to come back?

1441
00:56:15,776 --> 00:56:15,976
Like.

1442
00:56:16,876 --> 00:56:20,157
how do you deal with the, like, over time,

1443
00:56:20,257 --> 00:56:23,257
people getting bored of restarting over again,

1444
00:56:23,417 --> 00:56:26,418
even though it's something new, it's the same new thing?

1445
00:56:26,438 --> 00:56:28,418
Yeah.

1446
00:56:28,798 --> 00:56:30,799
So the question was how do we deal with meta burnout,

1447
00:56:31,139 --> 00:56:33,399
which is basically the next level above of, you know,

1448
00:56:33,599 --> 00:56:35,499
having to come back every league until eventually

1449
00:56:35,659 --> 00:56:37,060
you come back so many times.

1450
00:56:37,420 --> 00:56:39,500
This is partly what our big, big expansions are for.

1451
00:56:39,540 --> 00:56:40,800
That's the next meta level above there,

1452
00:56:40,820 --> 00:56:43,821
the 2.0.0, the 3.0.0, next year's 4.0.0 is gonna be nuts.

1453
00:56:44,341 --> 00:56:46,662
Anyway, those are the things that really drag people back.

1454
00:56:47,063 --> 00:56:50,304
And like, I mean, I was talking to a good friend of mine who works at Jinx,

1455
00:56:50,364 --> 00:56:53,686
and he actually started playing Path of Exile way back in the early alpha.

1456
00:56:54,066 --> 00:56:56,548
And he was saying he recently returned to it, has been having a blast.

1457
00:56:56,948 --> 00:56:59,409
And this is something where he took several years off, but now he's back,

1458
00:56:59,829 --> 00:57:02,331
spending money and playing characters, and it's all good.

1459
00:57:03,411 --> 00:57:03,851
Cool, thanks.

1460
00:57:03,891 --> 00:57:04,072
Thanks.

1461
00:57:06,824 --> 00:57:17,728
Hi, great talk. You mentioned that you generate content in the background so that it's just ready for use in expansion because that's the only way to do it.

1462
00:57:18,088 --> 00:57:21,490
What about tools engineering and things like that? How do you handle that?

1463
00:57:22,090 --> 00:57:22,790
The tools you were saying?

1464
00:57:24,023 --> 00:57:28,704
We have a tools team internally, so the question was what do we do about tools in terms of content generation and so on.

1465
00:57:28,724 --> 00:57:32,865
We have a tools team internally, probably not as large as we should have, it's obviously an evolution over many years,

1466
00:57:33,145 --> 00:57:34,765
and they're trying to stay abreast of the tools.

1467
00:57:35,025 --> 00:57:40,047
We made a decision a few years ago that instead of replacing our engine, we were just going to make it as modern as we can,

1468
00:57:40,067 --> 00:57:44,188
so we have a lot of advanced stuff there now which is beginning to be used in the game,

1469
00:57:44,508 --> 00:57:46,428
and therefore the tools team really got scaled up a bit.

1470
00:57:47,468 --> 00:57:49,609
It's kind of the heart of things like procedural generation.

1471
00:57:49,869 --> 00:57:51,169
When we do our, I don't know,

1472
00:57:51,229 --> 00:57:53,070
we revamp the Atlas of Worlds occasionally,

1473
00:57:53,090 --> 00:57:54,310
and that now has a complicated tool

1474
00:57:54,330 --> 00:57:55,670
that lets people move all the stuff around,

1475
00:57:56,170 --> 00:57:59,631
and it really is paying off in terms of time

1476
00:57:59,651 --> 00:58:00,951
and effort invested in the tool stuff.

1477
00:58:01,431 --> 00:58:03,272
It's kind of completely separate from the concept

1478
00:58:03,312 --> 00:58:04,792
of making art assets, though, for the most part.

1479
00:58:04,812 --> 00:58:06,212
I mean, the tool we're using to make this,

1480
00:58:06,493 --> 00:58:08,153
you know, endless supply of content is Maya,

1481
00:58:08,513 --> 00:58:10,513
for the most part, but all of the stuff we use

1482
00:58:10,533 --> 00:58:11,774
to actually hook it up into the game

1483
00:58:11,814 --> 00:58:13,134
is our ever-evolving set of tools,

1484
00:58:13,154 --> 00:58:14,974
which certainly pays off when we improve it.

1485
00:58:15,835 --> 00:58:16,315
One more question?

1486
00:58:17,543 --> 00:58:18,304
Hi, thanks for the talk.

1487
00:58:19,004 --> 00:58:20,205
Love the entertainment from it too.

1488
00:58:20,285 --> 00:58:22,587
So my question was for the economy part of it.

1489
00:58:22,607 --> 00:58:24,749
You said you reset the economy each time you do a release.

1490
00:58:24,949 --> 00:58:25,089
Yes.

1491
00:58:25,209 --> 00:58:26,550
How do you do that without upsetting users

1492
00:58:26,570 --> 00:58:29,532
who have spent for like all this effort and put into it?

1493
00:58:29,793 --> 00:58:31,974
This is a great question and something that I did gloss over.

1494
00:58:32,034 --> 00:58:33,736
So we reset the economy with a release,

1495
00:58:33,796 --> 00:58:34,917
but who wants to be reset?

1496
00:58:34,937 --> 00:58:35,717
That sounds really bad.

1497
00:58:35,958 --> 00:58:37,999
The way we do it is we make a new economy

1498
00:58:38,259 --> 00:58:40,081
and we say, you should play the release in that one.

1499
00:58:40,381 --> 00:58:41,802
and you've still got your old characters.

1500
00:58:41,842 --> 00:58:43,263
So we have what's called standard league,

1501
00:58:43,603 --> 00:58:45,985
where all the characters from the past economies get moved.

1502
00:58:46,005 --> 00:58:49,007
You're welcome to play there, maybe 15, 10% of players do play there.

1503
00:58:49,507 --> 00:58:52,069
And you've still got all the characters you've ever played in Path of Exile.

1504
00:58:52,329 --> 00:58:56,012
But the exciting place, where the economy isn't trashed with all the old items,

1505
00:58:56,332 --> 00:58:56,992
is the new league.

1506
00:58:57,233 --> 00:59:00,695
And so we make sure that the new league content is generally only available in the new economy.

1507
00:59:00,935 --> 00:59:02,916
So that's kind of your reward for starting a new character.

1508
00:59:03,177 --> 00:59:04,638
And this took a little while to train players,

1509
00:59:04,938 --> 00:59:06,499
but it really works well. It's the lifeblood.

1510
00:59:06,519 --> 00:59:08,420
I wouldn't be here if it wasn't for the fact that this works.

1511
00:59:09,445 --> 00:59:10,380
Well, thank you very much, everyone.

